---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../../components/PageHeader.astro";

const logo = "<(.____.)>";
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`Merch — ${logo}`}
  description="A future shop section for the website."
  lang="en"
>
  <PageHeader
    title="Merch"
    description="A future shop section for the website. No cart, checkout, or commercial machinery yet."
  />

  <section>
    <p>
      Merch is coming later. In the first version of the website, this page
      exists as a foundation for a future shop section, not as a full store.
    </p>

    <p>
      Right now, the priority is to build content, projects, and an audience.
      Selling mugs to an empty hallway would be poetic, but not especially useful.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Planned categories</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>stickers;</li>
      <li>T-shirts;</li>
      <li>mugs;</li>
      <li>posters;</li>
      <li>digital materials.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Principle</h2>

    <p>
      First, the website should become a living place with materials, projects,
      and a recognizable style. The shop comes later.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>